Linked lists are a dynamic data structure where each element points to the next element.

**Example:**
```c
// C example
struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node* next;
};

int main() {
    struct Node* head = NULL;
    struct Node* node = malloc(sizeof(struct Node));
    node->data = 1;
    node->next = NULL;
    head = node;
    return 0;
}
```

